eNCA's Govan Whittles is following this story. Courtesy #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG -  The African Transformation Movement is demanding that President Cyril Ramaphosa and the police be held accountable for the robbery and theft of an undisclosed amount of money at the president's Phala Phala farm in Limpopo. READ: Parliament declines to probe Phala Phala theft allegations The party has deposed a statement at the office of the Independent Police Investigative Directorate and believes IPID will continue with the investigations. Watch the video above for more details​​​​​​.